# .lock merge=keepours

# ============================================================================
# LINE ENDING RULES FOR WINDOWS
# ============================================================================

# If working on Windows with CRLF, force LF for these:
# (already done above with eol=lf)

# If working on Unix with LF, force CRLF for these (rare):
# *.bat eol=crlf
# *.cmd eol=crlf

# ============================================================================
# NOTES & BEST PRACTICES
# ============================================================================
#
# ðŸ“‹ ATTRIBUTE QUICK REFERENCE:
#
# Normalization:
#   text=auto          Auto-detect and normalize
#   eol=lf             Force Unix line endings
#   eol=crlf           Force Windows line endings
#
# Classification:
#   text               Git will normalize
#   binary             Git won't modify
#
# Diffs:
#   diff=type          Use specific diff driver
#   -diff              Disable diff
#
# Merge:
#   merge=type         Use specific merge strategy
#   -merge             No merge (use 'ours' or 'theirs' manually)
#
# Other:
#   delta              Delta compression for large files
#   ident              $Id$ keyword substitution
#   export-ignore      Exclude from git archive
#
# ============================================================================
# WORKFLOW TIPS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Apply .gitattributes to existing repo:
#    git add .gitattributes
#    git commit -m "Add .gitattributes for line ending normalization"
#    git rm -rf --cached .
#    git reset --hard HEAD
#
# 2. Normalize existing line endings:
#    git add -A
#    git status (check changes)
#    git commit -m "Normalize line endings to LF"
#
# 3. Check current attributes:
#    git check-attr -a <filename>
#
# 4. Debug merge/diff issues:
#    git config --list | grep merge
#    git config --list | grep diff
#
# 5. Export without certain files:
#    git archive --format=tar HEAD | tar -x
#    (Uses export-ignore settings)
#
# ============================================================================
# TEAM COLLABORATION
# ============================================================================
#
# ALWAYS commit .gitattributes to repository:
#   - Ensures consistent line ending handling across team
#   - Prevents CRLF/LF conflicts
#   - Helps with cross-platform development (Mac/Linux/Windows)
#   - Improves diffs and merge conflict resolution
#
# Tell team to refresh their clone after .gitattributes changes:
#   git rm -rf --cached .
#   git reset --hard HEAD
#   git status (should be clean)
#
